{"TopicId":164006,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Multiple copies of ksp","CreatedByName":"AwesomeDude3664","CreatedById":180339,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T00:53:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AwesomeDude3664","CreatedById":180339,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T00:53:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHello everyone,\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0this is my first post in the forums. I was wondering if I could get a modded and unmodded install of ksp on my Mac.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave a great day!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dman979","CreatedById":123837,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T00:54:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223138526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164006\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501721604\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180339\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AwesomeDude3664\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, AwesomeDude3664 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EHello everyone,\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0this is my first post in the forums. I was wondering if I could get a modded and unmodded install of ksp on my Mac.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave a great day!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you can download multiple copies of KSP if you purchased it. I have multiple installs on my computer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T01:25:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223138528\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164006\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501721690\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022123837\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dman979\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Dman979 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you can download multiple copies of KSP if you purchased it. I have multiple installs on my computer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, and you can keep different versions. I have 1.0, 1.1, 1.2, and now, 1.3! I just wish I would have thought to keep .22, .24, .and .90\u00A0 Ah, those were the days!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T02:02:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd if you got the game through steam, you can just copy paste the files.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, welcome to the forums.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-08-03T02:03:00Z\u0022 title=\u002208/03/2017 02:03  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Jas0n\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T02:12:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have the GoG version on Linux, so don\u0027t really know if it\u0027s applicable to a Mac.\u00A0 But I simply made a copy of the GameData folder.\u00A0 Renamed it GameData.stock.\u00A0 I put all my mods into the original GameData folder.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf I want to play stock, I simply change the modded GameData folder to GameData.modded, and change GameData.stock to GameData.\u00A0 Now I\u0027m playing stock.\u00A0 And vice versa.\u00A0 This lets you access your saves under both \u0022versions\u0022 as well, since they\u0027re not kept in GameData.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screenshotat20170802.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/Screenshotat20170802.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T03:24:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, it\u0027s \u003Cem\u003Ehighly recommended\u003C/em\u003E to keep a pure stock copy around if you are going to be adding mods. As said above, you should be able to simply make an additional complete copy of the directory before you mod it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AwesomeDude3664","CreatedById":180339,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T04:07:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223138579\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164006\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501726346\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have the GoG version on Linux, so don\u0027t really know if it\u0027s applicable to a Mac.\u00A0 But I simply made a copy of the GameData folder.\u00A0 Renamed it GameData.stock.\u00A0 I put all my mods into the original GameData folder.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf I want to play stock, I simply change the modded GameData folder to GameData.modded, and change GameData.stock to GameData.\u00A0 Now I\u0027m playing stock.\u00A0 And vice versa.\u00A0 This lets you access your saves under both \u0022versions\u0022 as well, since they\u0027re not kept in GameData.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/Screenshotat20170802.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screenshotat20170802.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/Screenshotat20170802.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat seems simple enough! Thank you for all your replies!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T04:45:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223138616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164006\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501730674\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, it\u0027s \u003Cem\u003Ehighly recommended\u003C/em\u003E to keep a pure stock copy around if you are going to be adding mods. As said above, you should be able to simply make an additional complete copy of the directory before you mod it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yet another copy of [Gamedata] with your actual mods if you decide to add a new batch.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AwesomeDude3664","CreatedById":180339,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T05:33:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been thinking, can I just copy the squad GameData and place it into a new GameData folder, while renaming something Else?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T10:40:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/180339-awesomedude3664/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022180339\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/180339-awesomedude3664/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@AwesomeDude3664\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/179753-geonovast/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022179753\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/179753-geonovast/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Geonovast\u003C/a\u003E I\u0027d like to suggest an alternative - just make \u0022Gamedata.disabled\u0022 alongside \u0022Gamedata\u0022 and then just move everything unneeded out there - and back.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ETo make game \u0022stock\u0022, move everything out except \u0022Squad\u0022. Of course one can make a (bash/sh) script for that, since things are stored in subdirectories. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T13:40:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157058-kerbal101/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022157058\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157058-kerbal101/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kerbal101\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003EI think renaming two folders is much less work than selecting certain files and transferring possibly hundreds of MB back and forth.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlthough, writing a bash script to rename the folders isn\u0027t a bad idea...\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nOf course, from what I\u0027m seeing, mod management is much better handled with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E, which I tried, but it wasn\u0027t playing nice, and I hate fighting to get programs to work with mono/Wine, so I gave up.\u00A0 If someone ever created a native Linux mod manager like \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E, I\u0027d be all over it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T15:11:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/179753-geonovast/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022179753\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/179753-geonovast/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Geonovast\u003C/a\u003E moving, not transferring \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 Moving directories is similar to renaming\u003C/span\u003E them, since only inode information is changed - unless they are on different partitions \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E is \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/KSP-CKAN/CKAN/wiki/Installing-CKAN-on-Ubuntu-14.04\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eavailable\u003C/a\u003E for Linux, in case you need it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also easily \u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/desktop_entries\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ecreate\u003C/a\u003E shortcut to start it, if you need it and then drop it into \u003Cem\u003E~/.local/share/applications\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T15:19:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223138976\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164006\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501773082\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157058\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal101\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Kerbal101 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/179753-geonovast/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022179753\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/179753-geonovast/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Geonovast\u003C/a\u003E moving, not transferring \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 Moving directories is similar to renaming\u003C/span\u003E them, since only inode information is changed - unless they are on different partitions \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, brain fart.\u00A0 I still think it\u0027s more hassle than renaming the folders, but not by much.\u00A0 Same result, just different road to get there.\u00A0 It clicked when I was poking around to create the bash script that I remembered that moving files and renaming directories use the \u003Cem\u003Esame function\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223138976\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022164006\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221501773082\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157058\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal101\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Kerbal101 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E is \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/KSP-CKAN/CKAN/wiki/Installing-CKAN-on-Ubuntu-14.04\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eavailable\u003C/a\u003E for Linux, in case you need it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried that, and it would give me 3 or 4 errors, then wouldn\u0027t see the KSP installation.\u00A0 I\u0027ve only got 4-5 mods installed ATM, so it\u0027s not worth the hassle yet.\u00A0 It still uses mono, which is temperamental.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow what would be neat would be the ability to shut off an enable mods in game, but I realize that\u0027s not feasible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal101","CreatedById":157058,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-03T16:00:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/179753-geonovast/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022179753\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/179753-geonovast/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Geonovast\u003C/a\u003E Well, if you make two copies of 1Gb \u0022Squad\u0022 subfolder - and you are going to need that if you need two runnable Gamedata, the impact depends if you are using COW filesystem or not; so if you are not using BTRFS or ZFS then its 1Gb more compared to moving subfolders in/out on occasion. But yes, same function - I just shared my approach.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrankly speaking, I have not tried \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E yet and running 48 mods right now \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E KSP is technically written in Mono, just the standalone built-in version.. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AwesomeDude3664","CreatedById":180339,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-04T23:13:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRequest to close please. I\u0027ve figured out how to keep multiple copies. Thanks for all the replies!\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:kiss:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_kiss.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:kiss:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-08-05T03:35:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClosed by \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s request.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}